text: <@U0H4SJN11> i know you have a busy day elsewhere but I wanted to hear how rest of yesterday went in terms of adjusting the capacitive value AND updating Podium 1 to a halfsheet?

Switched podium to half sheet. Less false triggers. Then changed capacitance value. Had less range, but should have less false triggers. Didn't need to reset it after a minute to get rid of the false triggers.
good to know, i want to test more with nathan tomorrow.  in your opinion <@U0H4SJN11> the range was still acceptable?
Totally. Tiny hand was able to be about 1/4in above and still set it off.
One more note, I only changed one of the podiums to new capacitor value to give us comparison on site with people tomorrow. <30min to change both over to new capacitor.
<@U0H4SJN11|miguel> uploaded a file: <https://uncorked.slack.com/files/miguel/F48K2TKL3/winterlights2017_podium_v3.ino|winterlights2017_podium_v3.ino> and commented: Slightly more commented
